{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":38332,"name":"Graham Morrison","username":"degville","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/degville/{size}/2021_2.png","created_at":"2018-11-22T12:13:24.752Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe \u003ccode\u003enil\u003c/code\u003e plugin does not run any language-specific packaging logic, and is useful for parts with no source, or for parts with sources that don’t need to be compiled or packed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBy using the \u003cem\u003enil\u003c/em\u003e plugin, parts can be defined purely by using properties automatically included by Snapcraft, such as  \u003ccode\u003estage-packages\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor examples, search \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/search?q=path%3Asnapcraft.yaml+%22plugin%3A+nil%22\u0026amp;type=Code\"\u003eGitHub\u003c/a\u003e for projects already using the plugin.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eⓘ  This is a \u003cem\u003esnapcraft\u003c/em\u003e plugin. See \u003ca href=\"/t/snapcraft-plugins/4284\"\u003eSnapcraft plugins\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"/t/supported-plugins/8080\"\u003eSupported plugins\u003c/a\u003e for further details on how plugins are used.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2023-05-05T09:52:29.566Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":289,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":1435.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":8646,"topic_slug":"the-nil-plugin","display_username":"Graham Morrison","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/snapcraft-plugins/4284","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Snapcraft plugins","clicks":7},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/supported-plugins/8080","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Supported plugins","clicks":7},{"url":"https://github.com/search?q=path%3Asnapcraft.yaml+%22plugin%3A+nil%22\u0026type=Code","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":1},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/snap-documentation/11127","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Snap documentation","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":2772,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":true,"last_wiki_edit":"2023-05-05T09:52:29.583Z","can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":70752,"name":"Anatoli Babenia","username":"abitrolly","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/abitrolly/{size}/4528_2.png","created_at":"2020-05-26T13:03:00.972Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe description for this plugin is not completely correct. It is useful for \u003ccode\u003eparts\u003c/code\u003e with sources that don’t need to be compiled or packed, such as bash scripts. A better description would be that \u003ccode\u003enil\u003c/code\u003e plugin does not run any language specific packaging logic. At the same time, the docs could also contain a couple of  example illustrating how to include files into a \u003ccode\u003esnap\u003c/code\u003e without processing. I don’t see any examples for that in \u003ca href=\"https://snapcraft.io/docs/snapcraft-parts-metadata\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ehttps://snapcraft.io/docs/snapcraft-parts-metadata\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-05-26T13:03:00.972Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":17,"readers_count":16,"score":28.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":8646,"topic_slug":"the-nil-plugin","display_username":"Anatoli Babenia","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null